 <h4>Nonlinear Solution</h4>
 <p>
  The vertical displacement is the only unknown -
  <var>v</var>
  = ?
 </p>
 <p>We will use 3-rd order geometric nonlinearity theory for the solution. The equilibrium equations are then derived for the deformed state of the structure, as follows:</p>
 <p>Length and elongation in deformed state</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>l′</var>
   (
   <var>v</var>
   )  =
