   <i>mm</i>
   − 1 ·  ( 1273.37
   <i>kN</i>
   − 2000
   <i>kN</i>
   )  ·
   <span class="dvc">
    138.34
    <i>mm</i>
    − 0
    <i>mm</i>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    1273.37
    <i>kN</i>
    − 0
    <i>kN</i>
   </span>
   = 217.28
   <i>mm</i>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>We continue the calculations iteratively until we reach convergence.</p>
 <p>
  After
  <span class="eq">
   <var>n</var>
   = 37
  </span>
  iterations we get:
  <span class="eq">
   <var>v</var>
   <sub>2</sub>
   = 1105.46
   <i>mm</i>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Relative error -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>δ</var>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    <var>v</var>
    <sub>2</sub>
    −
    <var>v</var>
    <sub>1</sub>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    <var>v</var>
    <sub>2</sub>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
   </span>
   =
   <span class="dvc">
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    1105.46
    <i>mm</i>
    − 1105.46
    <i>mm</i>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
    1105.46
    <i>mm</i>
    <b class="b0">|</b>
   </span>
   = 2.28×10
   <sup>-7</sup>
  </span>
 </p>
 <h4>
  4. Solution with Calcpad
  <small>(modified Anderson-Bjork′s method)</small>
 </h4>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>v</var>
   =
   <span class="cond">$Root</span>
   {2 ·
   <var>F</var>
   <sub>y</sub>
   (
   <var>v</var>
   )  =
   <var>F</var>
   <sub>y</sub>
   ;
   <var>v</var>
   ∈ [0
   <i>mm</i>
   ; 200
   <i>m</i>
   ]} = 1105.46
   <i>mm</i>
  </span>
 </p>
